title: Fishworks! Pan-fried Brill With Creamed Caper Vermouth Sauce
summary: Need a gluten free main course? Fishworks! Pan-fried Brill With Creamed Caper Vermouth Sauce could be a great recipe to try. This recipe serves 4 and costs $3.56 per serving. One serving contains 719 calories, 29g of protein, and 23g of fat. Head to the store and pick up capers, dill, juice of lemon, and a few other things to make it today. To use up the double cream you could follow this main course with the Loaded Kit Kat Peanut Butter Brownies as a dessert. This recipe is liked by 1 foodies and cooks. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes approximately 16 minutes. With a spoonacular score of 75%, this dish is pretty good. Try Pan-fried Cod With Mustard-caper Sauce, Lobsters with Tarragon Vermouth Sauce, and Scallops with Pea Puree and Vermouth Sauce for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Fish can be paired with Pinot Grigio, Gruener Veltliner, and Pinot Noir. Fish is as diverse as wine, so it's hard to pick wines that go with every fish. A crisp white wine, such as a pinot grigio or Grüner Veltliner, will suit any delicately flavored white fish. Meaty, strongly flavored fish such as salmon and tuna can even handle a light red wine, such as a pinot noir. The Proverb Pinot Grigio Wine with a 5 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 13 dollars per bottle.
